description.narrative: 2019 was characterised by two cyclones (IDAI and Kenneth) which affected more than 1.8 million people, damaging economic and social infrastructures, mostly in Sofala and Cabo Delgado and triggered an L3 emergency response. As result of cyclones and floods, a major cholera outbreak with 7,050 cases and 8 deaths (Case fatality rate 0.1%) was reported affecting districts of Beira, Dondo, Nhamatanda, Buzi, Pemba, Mecufi and Metuge. Mozambique government with support from partners including UNICEF effectively provided a timely and strong response to the health needs of the affected population and prevented excess mortality due to natural disasters. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:01/01/2020
